quran[15]{c,v,t,f}:
  37,148,"And they believed; so We gave them enjoyment for a while."
  37,149,"Now ask them (O Muhammad صلى الله عليه وسلم): "
  37,150,"Or did We create the angels female while they were witnesses?"
  43,37,"And verily, they (Satans / devils) hinder them from the Path (of Allâh), but they think that they are guided aright!"
  43,38,"Till, when (such a one) comes to Us, he says [to his Qarîn (Satan / devil companion)] "
  43,39,"It will profit you not this Day (O you who turn away from Allâh’s remembrance and His worship) as you did wrong, (and) that you will be sharers (you and your Qarîn ) in the punishment."
  44,22,"(But they were aggressive), so he [Mûsâ (Moses)] called upon his Lord (saying): "
  44,23,"(Allâh said): "
  44,24,""
  45,13,"And has subjected to you all that is in the heavens and all that is in the earth; it is all as a favour and kindness from Him. Verily, in it are signs for a people who think deeply."
  45,14,"Say (O Muhammad صلى الله عليه و سلم) to the believers to forgive those who (harm them and) hope not for the Days of Allâh (i.e. His Recompense), that He may recompense people, according to what they have earned (i.e. to punish these disbelievers who harm the believers).{1}",footnotes:1:{45:14} The provision of this Verse was abrogated by the Verse of Jihâd (holy fighting) (Verse 9:36) against the polytheists.
  45,15,"Whosoever does a good deed, it is for his ownself, and whosoever does evil, it is against (his ownself). Then to your Lord you will be made to return."
  46,1,"Hâ-Mîm."
  46,2,"The revelation of the Book (this Qur’ân) is from Allâh, the All-Mighty, the All-Wise."
  46,3,"We created not the heavens and the earth and all that is between them except with truth, and for an appointed term. But those who disbelieve turn away from that whereof they are warned."